overview: The user initiated a request for a significant aesthetic improvement
  of their sleep questionnaire app, which they felt lacked visual appeal. The
  agent embarked on a comprehensive redesign, starting with a new, calming
  sleep-themed color palette using OKLCH values. This involved updating global
  CSS, main form layouts with subtle background effects and a redesigned
  progress indicator, and enhancing core UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and cards with improved visual feedback and transitions. All
  14 questionnaire sections were refactored to use a consistent card-style
  grouping, replacing generic gray boxes with themed borders and backgrounds. A
  critical console error regarding null input values was also addressed.
  Following initial implementation, user feedback highlighted remaining
  inconsistencies in the Report section's card headers and text colors, which
  the agent promptly rectified by unifying gradients and replacing all hardcoded
  colors with theme-based variables. The outcome is a significantly more
  polished, cohesive, and thematically appropriate application.
